{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InputStreamProtocol"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"close","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV"},{"text":"?) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}],"externalID":"s:3GIO19InputStreamProtocolPAAE5close11cancellableSbAA14CancellableRefVSg_tKF","extendedModule":"GIO","roleHeading":"Instance Method","title":"close(cancellable:)","symbolKind":"method","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"role":"symbol"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"close","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef"},{"text":"? = nil) ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Once the stream is closed, all other operations will return ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"closed"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Closing a stream multiple times will not return an error."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Streams will be automatically closed when the last reference","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is dropped, but you might want to call this function to make sure"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"resources are released as early as possible."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Some streams might keep the backing store of the stream (e.g. a file descriptor)","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"open after the stream is closed. See the documentation for the individual","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"stream for details."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On failure the first error that happened will be reported, but the close","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"operation will finish as much as possible. A stream that failed to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"close will still return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"closed"},{"type":"text","text":" for all operations. Still, it"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is important to check and report the error to the user.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"text":" is not ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", then the operation can be cancelled by","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"triggering the cancellable object from another thread. If the operation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"was cancelled, the error ","type":"text"},{"code":"cancelled","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be returned.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Cancelling a close will still leave the stream closed, but some streams"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can use a faster close that doesn’t block to e.g. check errors."}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/inputstreamprotocol\/close(cancellable:)-1fbj4"]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InputStreamProtocol\/close(cancellable:)-1fbj4","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text":"Closes the stream, releasing resources related to it.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/InputStreamProtocol/close(cancellable:)-1fbj4":{"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/inputstreamprotocol\/close(cancellable:)-1fbj4","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"close"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef"},{"text":"?) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InputStreamProtocol\/close(cancellable:)-1fbj4","abstract":[{"text":"Closes the stream, releasing resources related to it.","type":"text"}],"title":"close(cancellable:)","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/InputStreamProtocol":{"type":"topic","title":"InputStreamProtocol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"InputStreamProtocol"}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GInputStream"},{"type":"text","text":" is a base class for implementing streaming input."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/inputstreamprotocol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"InputStreamProtocol"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InputStreamProtocol","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/docume